Rating: 4
We love this dressing in our house. When I read the review about it being good enough to drink, I laughed. My daughter, who is 5 and a very picky eater, literally licks her plate clean. It is a pretty strong dressing, so I tend to use it primarily with butter lettuce rather than other lettuces than can be on the bitter side. It's a nice change from a vinagrette.

Rating: 4
WOW! I could drink this stuff, it is so delicious. Served it on a simple salad of arugula, thinly sliced green onion and chunks of fresh orange segments. I had some Four Vines Sophisticate left over from a few days ago, so I used that. Subbed unseasoned rice wine vinegar for the wine vinegar, and red onion for the green onions. This is a salad dressing to make, put in a fancy bottle or jar, and take as a hostess gift. This will be a Christmas gift for my foodie friends this year! This dressing is so good, you'll want to lick the plate clean!

Rating: 4
This is a great and easy salad dressing to make. I used Balsamic vinegar instead of red wine vinegar. The result was a richer dressing that went better with the wines I was serving at dinner.

